3. Project Workflow (Explain Like This)

You can say:

"The automation workflow starts when the cron scheduler triggers the Ansible playbook. The playbook connects to the remote server through SSH and performs several maintenance tasks."

Then explain steps:

1️⃣ Pre-maintenance checks

Disk usage (df -h)

Memory usage (free -m)

2️⃣ System update

Update package cache

Upgrade packages

Remove unused packages

3️⃣ Backup automation

Backup /etc directory using archive module

4️⃣ Conditional reboot

Reboot only if updates were installed

5️⃣ Logging

Maintenance execution time stored in log file

6️⃣ Cron scheduling

Weekly automation using cron


